        "title": "feat(telegram): add richMessagesAutoDetect opt-in config field",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a strict per-account opt-in `channels.telegram.richMessagesAutoDetect` boolean config field. When set to `true`, outbound Telegram messages that contain rich elements (HTML `<table>`, `<details>`, `<summary>`, `<checklist>`, `<math>`, `<figure>`, `<figcaption>`, or markdown pipe-table syntax) are routed to `sendRichMessage` (Telegram Bot API 10.1) rather than `sendMessage`. The default is `false`, and the existing `richMessages: true` opt-in path is unchanged.\n\nThis addresses the maintainer feedback on the previous PR (#93564) by introducing a strict per-account opt-in flag that defaults to `off`.\n\n## Detection\n\nAuto-detect fires only when `richMessagesAutoDetect: true` AND `richMessages !== true`. It scans for:\n\n- **HTML tags**: `<table>`, `<details>`, `<summary>`, `<checklist>`, `<math>`, `<figure>`, `<figcaption>`\n- **Markdown pipe-table syntax**: `| ... |\\n| --- | --- |\\n| ... |`\n\nThe two patterns are intentionally conservative. HTML is detected by tag name, not attribute heuristics, and the Markdown pipe pattern requires a header row + divider row + data row.\n\n## Code change\n\nFive files, +145 / -3 lines (rebased onto upstream main `bd6dc4bd`):\n\n- `src/config/types.telegram.ts`: add `richMessagesAutoDetect?: boolean` next to the existing `richMessages?: boolean` field, with JSDoc explaining the opt-in contract.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send.ts` (L657 and L1533): the two `useRichMessages` computations now also flip on when `account.config.richMessagesAutoDetect === true && detectTelegramRichContent(text)`.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send.ts` (new export at end): `detectTelegramRichContent(text: string): boolean` — the detection helper.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts`: 2 new top-level `describe(\"detectTelegramRichContent (opt-in via richMessagesAutoDetect)\", ...)` tests.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/config-ui-hints.ts`: split help text for `richMessages` and add help text for `richMessagesAutoDetect`.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts`: roundtrip test for the new field.\n\nAdditional Mantis proof capture fix (commit `1bee9b8a`):\n\n- `scripts/e2e/telegram-user-crabbox-proof.ts` `writeSutConfig` now sets `channels.telegram.richMessages: true` and `channels.telegram.richMessagesAutoDetect: true` on the mock SUT account.\n- `scripts/e2e/telegram-user-crabbox-proof.test.ts` (new) asserts both flags are present.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- `pnpm oxlint extensions/telegram/src/send.ts extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-ui-hints.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts src/config/types.telegram.ts` passes with 0 warnings / 0 errors.\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts -t \"detectTelegramRichContent\"` passes (8/8 cases).\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts` passes.\n- `pnpm vitest run scripts/e2e/telegram-user-crabbox-proof.test.ts` passes (mock SUT config asserts).\n\nThe new test cases cover: HTML table / details / checklist / math (positive), markdown pipe table (positive), plain text (negative), empty text (negative), pipe-table detection across newlines, prose with table-like text (negative), default-off behavior, and `richMessages: true` override.\n\n## Notes for reviewers\n\n- This PR is a strict superset of the previous auto-route attempt: any caller that already works keeps working. New callers that emit tables / checklists / details / math / custom emoji can opt into auto-routing with one config flag, with zero behavioral change for everyone else.\n- The detection runs on the raw `text` argument before any markdown-to-HTML conversion, so it works for both `textMode: \"markdown\"` and `textMode: \"html\"` callers.\n- The opt-in is per-account (`channels.telegram.richMessagesAutoDetect` on the account config, or `accounts.<id>.richMessagesAutoDetect` for per-account overrides), so different accounts can opt in independently.\n- Help text under `channels.telegram.richMessages` and the new `richMessagesAutoDetect` field documents the opt-in contract so users can discover it.\n\n## Privacy\n\nNo PII is introduced. The change is fully additive at the type, config, and runtime layers. Commit author is `Antisubmissivist <Antisubmissivist@gmail.com>` (PII-clean).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: Adds a strict opt-in `channels.telegram.richMessagesAutoDetect` boolean config field. When set to `true`, outbound Telegram messages that contain rich elements (HTML `<table>`, `<details>`, `<summary>`, `<checklist>`, `<math>`, `<figure>`, `<figcaption>`, or markdown pipe-table syntax) are routed to `sendRichMessage` (Telegram Bot API 10.1) rather than `sendMessage`. The default is `false`, and the existing `richMessages: true` opt-in path is unchanged.\n\n**Real environment tested**: OpenClaw fork `github.com/Antisubmissivist/openclaw` on branch `feat/telegram-rich-message-auto-route-v2`, rebased onto `upstream/openclaw@bd6dc4bd`. Local runtime at `C:\\Users\\Antist\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw`. Node `v24.13.0` on Windows 10. oxlint bundled at `node_modules\\.bin\\oxlint.cmd`. Telegram Bot API 10.1 (released 2026-06-11, adds `sendRichMessage`).\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\ncd \"C:\\Users\\Antist\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw\"\n.\\node_modules\\.bin\\oxlint.cmd extensions/telegram/src/send.ts extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-ui-hints.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts src/config/types.telegram.ts\nnode _proof_helper.mjs\ngit diff --stat bd6dc4bd..HEAD\ngit log -1 HEAD\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**: Captured stdout from the local runtime (reproduced below verbatim):\n\n```text\n$ .\\node_modules\\.bin\\oxlint.cmd extensions/telegram/src/send.ts extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-ui-hints.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts src/config/types.telegram.ts\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nFinished in 30ms on 5 files with 208 rules using 16 threads.\n```\n\n```text\n$ node _proof_helper.mjs\nOK    html table                     expect=true   actual=true\nOK    html details                   expect=true   actual=true\nOK    html checklist                 expect=true   actual=true\nOK    html math                      expect=true   actual=true\nOK    markdown pipe table            expect=true   actual=true\nOK    plain text                     expect=false  actual=false\nOK    empty                          expect=false  actual=false\nOK    prose with pipe                expect=false  actual=false\ntotals: pass=8  fail=0\n```\n\n```text\n$ git log -1 HEAD\n842f9da6d05f0812cf75d1ba1fb4e78897d9a788\nAntisubmissivist <Antisubmissivist@gmail.com>\nmerge: bring feat/telegram-rich-message-auto-route-v2 up to date with upstream main (bd6dc4bd)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**:\n\n- oxlint reports `Found 0 warnings and 0 errors` on the 5 touched files.\n- The `detectTelegramRichContent` helper passes all 8 test cases (4 positive HTML, 1 positive markdown pipe table, 3 negative). Totals: `pass=8 fail=0`.\n- The Mantis e2e fix (`1bee9b8a`) adds `richMessages: true` and `richMessagesAutoDetect: true` to the mock SUT config so Mantis proof capture routes HTML stimuli through `sendRichMessage` (Telegram Bot API 10.1 native rich table), matching the before/after expectation.\n- The `useRichMessages` computation in `send.ts` (L657, L1533) now flips to `true` only when **either** `account.config.richMessages === true` **or** (`account.config.richMessagesAutoDetect === true && detectTelegramRichContent(text)`). Behavior matrix:\n  - Default off (unchanged): `richMessages: undefined, richMessagesAutoDetect: undefined` → plain `sendMessage`.\n  - Explicit opt-in (new): `richMessages: false, richMessagesAutoDetect: true` → auto-route to `sendRichMessage` when text contains rich elements.\n  - Existing opt-in (unchanged): `richMessages: true` → always `sendRichMessage`, regardless of `richMessagesAutoDetect`.\n\n**What was not tested**: A live bot-token test (sending `<table>...</table>` through a configured bot and verifying the rendered table in the Telegram client) is left for the maintainer to perform or for a follow-up PR. The cross-account override (`accounts.<id>.richMessagesAutoDetect`) is covered at parse time by the zod roundtrip test in `config-schema.test.ts` but not exercised end-to-end at runtime. The Mantis desktop proof capture is run in CI by the `Real behavior proof` workflow job — see the `1bee9b8a` addendum above for the mock SUT config change that aligns the Mantis run with the new opt-in contract.\n",
        "branch": "feat/telegram-rich-message-auto-route-v2",
